Isobaric Normalization

Before conducting any analyses, the data must undergo isobaric normalization. Figure 1 shows the data before and after undergoing isobaric normalization.

Figure 1: Data before and after undergoing isobaric normalization

Filters

We filter out by the msgf value. For this dataset, the msgf threshold is 2.7113e-08 and sum up and peptide redundancies.

Protein Quantitation

We then run protein quantitation on the data.

Reverse Hits/Contaminants

We then remove reverse hits and contaminants that may still be present in the dataset.

Results

We can look at the number of significant fold changes between all comparisons. Figure 2 demonstrates the number of significant fold changes by each pairwise comparison in both a bar plot and a volcano plot.

Figure 2: Significant fold changes by both bar plot (left) and volcano plot (right)
